❌lead to major wage gains
❌usher in 3%+ GDP growth
❌boost business investment
❌pay for themselves

Because the most recent GOP tax cuts were such a success? https://www.washingtonpost.com/us-policy/2019/10/31/white-house-officials-ramp-up-new-tax-cut-talks-trump-seeks-sharp-contrast-with-democrats/?hpid=hp_rhp-more-top-stories_trump-tax-1pm%3Ahomepage%2Fstory-ans …

BREAKING: Consumer spending on goods and services increased just 0.2% in September, @BEA_News reported, falling short of analyst forecasts. Wages and salaries were unchanged from the prior month. #EconTwitter https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-10-31/u-s-consumer-spending-jobless-claims-signal-caution-on-economy …

Chairman Jerome Powell is now speaking to reporters after the #Fed's decision to cut interest rates. He notes the economy is running at a moderate pace, as consumer spending offsets declines in exports and business investment. Check out this key clip. #EconTwitter pic.twitter.com/9E33KUev4h

#Fed statement also highlights the following:
•Job market is strong
•Economy growing at moderate pace
•Business investment, exports weak
•Inflation below target
•Target range for rates is 1.5-1.75%
•Two voted against the quarter-point cut https://www.cnbc.com/2019/10/30/fed-decision-interest-rates-cut.html …

#Fed lowers rate, saying it "will continue to monitor the implications of incoming information for the economic outlook," and deletes phrase from prior statement that it would "act as appropriate to sustain the expansion." That may increase bets that cutting is over. #EconTwitter

From Vice Chair @RepMaloney: "Clearly the GOP’s wasteful tax cuts for the wealthy are not delivering the sustained boost they promised, while the White House’s haphazard trade policies and general chaos are undermining business confidence." https://www.jec.senate.gov/public/index.cfm/democrats/press-releases?ID=EE58BD91-B3CF-4DA4-A3D7-C930F998D264 …

"I am deeply concerned the president’s misguided policies and actions will cause the economy to slow even further and hurt the labor market, potentially resulting in job losses and weaker wage gains."—Vice Chair @RepMaloney

One big takeaway from the GDP report is that business investment (which was supposed to boom after GOP tax cuts took effect) is shrinking. As @IanShepherdson is quoted as saying in the @nytimes, "there’s been a big drop in business confidence, across the board." pic.twitter.com/AmNYpHE5Jc

Vice Chair @RepMaloney on the GDP report: "This is the second straight quarter of lackluster growth and all but confirms that we’re experiencing a pronounced economic deceleration, despite the president’s past pledges of 3-6 percent growth." #EconTwitter
 https://www.jec.senate.gov/public/index.cfm/democrats/press-releases?ID=EE58BD91-B3CF-4DA4-A3D7-C930F998D264 …

We agree caring for people w/mental illness is important. Our report shows the lethality of guns as a suicide tool is driving up the death rate. Most who attempt suicide with a gun die. Most who try by other means survive, & most of those say they wouldn't attempt suicide again.

Our report does address mental illness: "Research has found a correlation between guns and suicide rates, even when controlling for race and gender as well as other factors associated with suicide like age, education, poverty, unemployment, serious mental illness..."
(4/4) Today's #SenateLatinoSummit features actress & activist @EvaLongoria and chef & humanitarian @chefjoseandres. It's streaming live on Facebook.  https://www.facebook.com/USSenateDemocrats/ …

(3/4) The report found Latinos are more likely to be in the labor force than the population as a whole, while they also are more likely to be entrepreneurs, as nearly one in four new businesses in this country is Latino-owned. #SenateLatinoSummit pic.twitter.com/5rZqVkvhgv

(2/4) Latinos account for $2.3T in economic activity, which would rank as the world's 8th largest economy. As Vice Chair @RepMaloney noted, "not only our future, but our present as well, depends upon Latino economic contributions to make America thrive." #SenateLatinoSummit

(1/4) Check out the #SenateLatinoSummit today and celebrate contributions of Latinos in the U.S. According to a recent report by the JEC and @HispanicCaucus, by 2060 roughly one in four people living in the country will be Latino or of Hispanic heritage.  https://www.jec.senate.gov/public/index.cfm/democrats/press-releases?ID=D47802CE-2A92-437F-A583-DBAC8D164AE2 … pic.twitter.com/o8046UaHU9

Our report shows that suicide is most often an impulse decision. Most people who attempt suicide with a gun die. Most people who try by other means survive, and most of those survivors say they wouldn't attempt suicide again.

(6/6) “If we could reduce firearm suicides, we would make substantial progress in addressing the gun violence epidemic in America. Now the challenge and the responsibility before Americans is to do something about it”—@RepMaloney. #EndGunViolence https://www.jec.senate.gov/public/index.cfm/democrats/press-releases?ID=F61E716D-BD62-4C35-ABFC-FE9D2A485BBA …

(5/6) And firearm suicide is much more prevalent among white men, while older Americans are also at high risk. Seniors 65 and older accounted for over 8,600 of 47,000+ suicides in 2017, while adults 85 or older were among the most likely to take their own life. #EndGunViolence pic.twitter.com/jvFAaa3OCZ

(4/6) Geography is a strong predictor of gun suicide rates in the U.S. Those living in rural areas are almost 75% more likely to die by firearm suicide than those in cities. States that rank highest in terms of gun ownership also rank among the highest in firearm suicide rates. pic.twitter.com/i7KgFhxVhh

(3/6) According to a recent study (based on 2015 data), the firearm suicide rate is about 10-times higher in the U.S. than similar industrial nations. #EndGunViolence @Everytown @GiffordsCourage @bradybuzz @afspnational pic.twitter.com/lgMLtSn6MD

(2/6) While many people understandably think of guns in the context of mass shootings and other homicides, firearm suicides have long been the leading cause of gun deaths in America, the report finds. #EndGunViolence @Everytown @GiffordsCourage @bradybuzz @afspnational pic.twitter.com/LNJJWY1j7q
